{
  "stem": "2002.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, I was very disappointed that I couldn't go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But-- but I understood the [NON-ENGLISH] means to be a guard-- you know, to guard the country.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, you know, and to build a country.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And but they all, every one who went, you could see smiles on their faces.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Only [? sadder ?] that we had to leave other guys behind them, or other girls, before they went.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, activities also was we would met, and I would do get some teachings from-- we would go out, like [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know if you know what like [NON-ENGLISH] means.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's a Zionist picnic, to go out to the-- in the woods and the field.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we-- we would-- we would talk in the woods.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Be a lot of teaching, because the education system was very bad for Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So but some of them were luckier than I because, I guess, their parents were richer, and they could send the kids more to school.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- but the poor people had it tough to do anything.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So in the-- when I belonged to Shomer ha-Tsa'ir, I would be taught some education.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Let's move to 1939.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah. 1939 was-- was-- the town was very-- I don't know how to in English to explain.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We knew that's comin', because they are already, we heard on the radio.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was only one radio where they were-- I remember there was a store, they was selling bikes.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was one on the front door, was a small little radio.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you could hear that, that Hitler's preparing for-- for war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Is it 30 minutes?",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
